    https://sandbox.test.parku.io/v5

    Parku API v5 Reference

    API Endpoint: https://sandbox.test.parku.io/v5

    The parku API is organized around REST. Our API is designed to have predictable, resource-oriented URLs and to use HTTP response codes to indicate API errors. We use built-in HTTP features, like HTTP authentication and HTTP verbs, which can be understood by off-the-shelf HTTP clients. JSON will be returned in all responses from the API, including errors.

    Versions ¶

    • previous: v4

    • latest stable: v5

    Changes in v5 ¶

    • Replaced locations model with an hierarchical one. This affects the Locations Endpoint and Bookings Endpoint. Find the description of the new model at:

      • Location Model
      • Parking Space Group Model
      • First Level Cluster Model
      • Second Level Cluster Model

    • extended booking model with type, zone and payment

    • added onstreet endpoint

    • added stop a booking

    • added user payment methods

    • voucher endpoint removed

    Api definition files ¶

    • Swagger definition (readable by Postman)

    • Api Blueprint

    Attributes ¶

    Attributes ¶

    Access needs a private key.

    Example Request

    curl 'https://sandbox.test.parku.io/v5/attributes' \
    --insecure \
    --request POST \
    --user 012345678abcdef:parku \
    -H 'Content-Type: application/json' \
    -d @- << EOF
    {
      "key": "adac",
      "value": "12345"
    }
    EOF
    Headers
    Content-Type: application/json
    Authorization: Basic MDEyMzQ1Njc4YWJjZGVmOnBhcmt1
    Body
    {
  "key": "adac",
  "value": "12345"
}
    Schema
    {
  "type": "object",
  "properties": {
    "key": {
      "type": "string",
      "description": "The name of the attribute. Currently only 'adac' and 'test' are allowed"
    },
    "value": {
      "type": "string",
      "description": "The value of the attribute, eg. a membership number"
    }
  },
  "required": [
    "key",
    "value"
  ],
  "$schema": "http://json-schema.org/draft-04/schema#"
}

    Example Response

    200
    Headers
    Content-Type: application/json
    Body
    {
  "id": 32,
  "key": "adac",
  "value": "12345"
}

    Create a new Attribute ¶
    POST/attributes

    Request Attributes  (application/json)
    key
    string (required) Example: adac

    The name of the attribute. Currently only ‘adac’ and ‘test’ are allowed

    value
    string (required) Example: 12345

    The value of the attribute, eg. a membership number

    Example Request

    curl 'https://sandbox.test.parku.io/v5/attributes/32' \
    --insecure \
    --user 012345678abcdef:parku
    Headers
    Authorization: Basic MDEyMzQ1Njc4YWJjZGVmOnBhcmt1

    Example Response

    200
    Headers
    Content-Type: application/json
    Body
    {
  "id": 32,
  "key": "adac",
  "value": "12345"
}

    Retrieve an Attribute ¶
    GET/attributes/{attribute_id}

    URI Parameters
    attribute_id
    int (required) Example: 32

    The identifier of the attribute to be retrieved

    Authentication ¶

    Http Basic Auth ¶

    Authentication to the API occurs via HTTP Basic Auth. Provide your API key as the basic auth username. The password is always parku. All API requests must be made over HTTPS. Calls made over plain HTTP will fail. You must authenticate for all requests.

    Private and public keys ¶

    There are two types of keys: public and private. Public keys are used to obtain publicly available information (eg. parking spaces). Private keys are used to identify users. Whenever user information are requested or bookings on behalf of a user is made, the private key is necessary.

    Retrieving a private key ¶

    You retrieve a user specific private key by logging in as a user.

    Private vs. public urls ¶

    For the public urls you need a public key. With a private key you can access public urls.

    Bookings ¶

    Bookings ¶

    Access needs a private key.

    Example Request

    curl 'https://sandbox.test.parku.io/v5/bookings' \
    --insecure \
    --request POST \
    --user 012345678abcdef:parku \
    -H 'Content-Type: application/json' \
    -d @- << EOF
    {
      "group_id": "00cd7cfd-e42d-11e2-8bf1-8a83f3373875",
      "date_start": "2016-10-27T09:10:20+00:00",
      "date_end": "2016-10-27T10:10:20+00:00",
      "license_plate": "B-AB 1234",
      "phone_number": "+493057701872",
      "payment": [
        {
          "type": "paypal",
          "amount": 1200,
          "payload": "PAY-1CM399047K4649003KM4WJQQ"
        }
      ],
      "payment_method": {
        "id": "1000bb3e-506d-11e5-9781-d43d7eece658",
        "type": "immediate"
      },
      "required_fields": {
        "car_color": "red",
        "number_of_passengers": "5"
      },
      "user_metadata": {
        "latitude": 52.521381,
        "longitude": 13.3920158
      }
    }
    EOF
    Headers
    Content-Type: application/json
    Authorization: Basic MDEyMzQ1Njc4YWJjZGVmOnBhcmt1
    Body
    {
  "group_id": "00cd7cfd-e42d-11e2-8bf1-8a83f3373875",
  "date_start": "2016-10-27T09:10:20+00:00",
  "date_end": "2016-10-27T10:10:20+00:00",
  "license_plate": "B-AB 1234",
  "phone_number": "+493057701872",
  "payment": [
    {
      "type": "paypal",
      "amount": 1200,
      "payload": "PAY-1CM399047K4649003KM4WJQQ"
    }
  ],
  "payment_method": {
    "id": "1000bb3e-506d-11e5-9781-d43d7eece658",
    "type": "immediate"
  },
  "required_fields": {
    "car_color": "red",
    "number_of_passengers": "5"
  },
  "user_metadata": {
    "latitude": 52.521381,
    "longitude": 13.3920158
  }
}
    Schema
    {
  "type": "object",
  "properties": {
    "group_id": {
      "type": "string",
      "description": "The ID of the location you get returned from the locations request"
    },
    "date_start": {
      "type": "string",
      "description": "start date and time of the booking"
    },
    "date_end": {
      "type": "string",
      "description": "end date and time of the booking"
    },
    "license_plate": {
      "type": "string",
      "description": "The license plate of the used car.\n\nGet all cars of a user from the [cars](#user-cars-get) request."
    },
    "phone_number": {
      "type": "string",
      "description": "The phone number.\n\nGet all phone numbers of a user from the [phone_numbers](`#user-phone_numbers-get`) request."
    },
    "payment": {
      "type": "array",
      "items": {
        "type": "object",
        "properties": {
          "type": {
            "enum": [
              "paypal",
              "credit",
              "braintree"
            ],
            "description": "The payment method."
          },
          "amount": {
            "type": "number",
            "description": "The amount to pay with this method as an integer where `amount = 100 * decimal_amount`."
          },
          "payload": {
            "type": "string",
            "description": "The information of the payment provider to perform a payment.  Required for `paypal` and `braintree`.\n\nThe field `provider_info` should contain required payment information.\nTypically you just forward the info from your request to the payment provider into this field.\n\n* **PayPal**\n    You can either use the complete PayPal response or just add the payment ID:\n    ```\n    payments.payload=PAY-1CM399047K4649003KM4WJQQ\n    ```\n\n* **Braintree**\n    There are two ways to pay with braintree:\n    1. _CreditCard-ID_\n\n        Retrieve the Card ID through the payment endpoint and add it to the request:\n\n        ```\n        payments.payload[id]=gphsyb\n        ```\n    2. _CreditCard Credentials_\n\n        ```\n        payments.payload[number]=EncryptedCreditCardNumber\n        payments.payload[expiration_date]=EncryptedExpirationDate\n        payments.payload[cvv]=EncryptedCvv\n        ```"
          }
        },
        "required": [
          "type",
          "amount"
        ]
      },
      "description": "The payments to use for paying (optional). This can be credits, coupons,\npaypal and braintree payments that have been authorized on the frontend."
    },
    "payment_method": {
      "type": "object",
      "properties": {
        "id": {
          "type": "string",
          "description": "the payment method id,\n\nonly needed if type is `immediate`"
        },
        "type": {
          "enum": [
            "immediate"
          ],
          "description": "How to execute the payment. Currently only immediate\n\npayments are supported."
        }
      },
      "required": [
        "type"
      ],
      "description": "The payment method to use for paying. This method will be used for paying the fee of the booking\nafter all payments from the `payments` field have been applied. E.g. if you provided a 5 Euro\nvoucher via `payments`, the payment method will be used on 5 Euro less than the actual booking fee."
    },
    "required_fields": {
      "type": "object",
      "properties": {
        "car_color": {
          "type": "string",
          "description": "the car color"
        },
        "number_of_passengers": {
          "type": "string",
          "description": "the number of passengers"
        }
      },
      "description": "Parking space required fields defined in the locations request. The required fields should contain all required fields defined in location. All values should be sent as strings."
    },
    "user_metadata": {
      "type": "object",
      "properties": {
        "latitude": {
          "type": "number",
          "description": "users latitude"
        },
        "longitude": {
          "type": "number",
          "description": "users longitude"
        }
      },
      "description": "Additional information about a user (optional). This is for example latitude/longitude parameters\nfor the users current position."
    }
  },
  "required": [
    "group_id",
    "date_start",
    "date_end",
    "license_plate",
    "phone_number"
  ],
  "$schema": "http://json-schema.org/draft-04/schema#"
}

    violation
    object

    violation id

    status
    string Example: active

    status of the booking, can be active or canceled for offstreet bookings and running, finished or ‘canceled’ for onstreet bookings

    type
    string Example: offstreet

    Choices: offstreet onstreet

    the booking type

    group_id
    string Example: 123c4826-4e28-11e3-a675-d43d7eece53d

    the id of the booked parking space group

    parking_space_code
    string Example: ABCDE

    the code of the booked parking space

    location
    object 

    the location that was booked, only available if type is offstreet.

    location.id
    string Example: e644e4bc-4c5c-11e4-a24a-d43d7eecedd2

    unique identifier of the location used for referencing.

    location.address_slug
    string Example: dorfstrasse-11

    latitude part of the location geo coordinate

    location.longitude
    number Example: 13.19988

    longitude part of the location geo

    string Example: Dorfstraße

    the street name of the location without number

    location.street_number
    string Example: 11

    the street number of the location

    location.postcode
    string Example: 16761

    post code of the location

    location.city
    string Example: Hennigsdorf

    city of the location

    location.country
    string Example: Deutschland

    country of the location in 2 character encoding country of the location in 2

    character encoding

    location.bookable
    boolean Example: true

    true if that locations can be booked via the parku API, false if the location

    is purely providing information

    location.payment
    object 

    available payment methods and types for the current user in this location. The payment methods and types depend on the private key of the logged in user. For locations requests using public keys these arrays will be empty.

    location.payment.methods
    array Example: [paypal]

    May Contain: paypal credits coupon braintree ideal

    Possible payment methods for this location and user

    location.payment.types
    array Example: [post]

    May Contain: post immediate

    Possible payment types for this location and user

    location.availability
    object 

    describes the availability of the location in relation to the request

    location.availability.current
    number Example: 0

    the number of parking spaces available in the group for the requested time period defined

    by start and endthe number of parking spaces available in the group for the requested time period defined by start and end

    location.availability.maximum
    number Example: 1

    the overall number of parking spaces at this group the overall number of parking spaces at

    this group

    location.availability.next_start
    string Example: 2016-...15:00:..

    the start of the next from now slot in which a parking space in this

    group is free and bookable, can be in the past

    location.availability.next_end
    string Example: 2016-...15:00:..

    the end of the next slot from now in which a parking space in this group

    is free and bookable, can be in the past

    location.parking_space_groups
    array 

    different parking space groups for this location. See Parking Space Group Data

    location.parking_space_groups[].id
    string Example: 1644c5dc-4c5c-11e4-a24a-d43d7eecedd2

    unique identifier of the location used for referencing.

    location.parking_space_groups[].type
    string Example: off-street

    Choices: off-street park-and-ride professional-garage airport-parking harbor-parking

    describes the type of location and can be one of the following.

    location.parking_space_groups[].description
    string Example: Doppelparkplatz. Jedoch nur für ein Auto zu vermieten.

    location.parking_space_groups[].image_urls
    array Example: [https://parku.de/images/parkingspace/020a81f5-c8b9-11e4-bfd2-d43d7eece658/640x286.jpg]

    urls of location images, can be empty

    location.parking_space_groups[].options
    array Example: [excess length]

    May Contain: excess length indoor disabled patio barrier charging station key_necessary long_term_booking surveillance valet_service

    describes which options are available at the location and can contains each of the following elements. The list can be empty.

    location.parking_space_groups[].support
    object 

    location.parking_space_groups[].support.phone_number
    string Example: +493012064329

    returns the support center phone number for this location

    location.parking_space_groups[].price
    object 

    location.parking_space_groups[].price.total
    number Example: 150

    the total price for booking a parking space of this group if start and end was provided, null otherwise.

    location.parking_space_groups[].price.currency
    string Example: EUR

    Choices: EUR CHF

    the currency of the price

    location.parking_space_groups[].price.period
    string Example: timeframe

    Choices: timeframe day week month

    contains the period for how long the price is valid, can be null if start or end was not provided

    location.parking_space_groups[].price.rate_hourly
    number Example: 10

    shows the price for per hour

    location.parking_space_groups[].price.rate_daily
    number Example: 100

    shows the price per day

    location.parking_space_groups[].price.rate_weekly
    number Example: 300

    shows the price per week

    location.parking_space_groups[].price.rate_monthly
    number Example: 1500

    shows the price per month

    location.parking_space_groups[].user_owned
    boolean Example: false

    true if the user who requested the location is also the owner of the parking space. This allows to determine if the user could block the parking space from bookings.

    location.parking_space_groups[].settings
    object 

    provides booking requirements for the location. The settings of a location are used in favor of the global settings that can be found in the settings endpoint.

    location.parking_space_groups[].settings.bookable_range_start
    number Example: -15

    start of the range wherein a booking is allowed in minutes from now.

    location.parking_space_groups[].settings.bookable_range_end
    number Example: 43200

    end of the range wherein a booking is allowed in minutes from now. end of the range wherein a booking is allowed in minutes from now.

    location.parking_space_groups[].settings.booking_duration_min
    number Example: 30

    minimum duration of a booking in minutes.

    location.parking_space_groups[].settings.booking_duration_max
    number Example: 43200

    maximum duration of a booking in minutes.

    location.parking_space_groups[].required_fields
    array Example: [car_registration_number]

    May Contain: car_registration_number car_make car_model car_colour number_of_passengers car_dropoff_time car_pickup_time outbound_flight_terminal outbound_flight_number inbound_flight_number outbound_flight_time inbound_flight_time user_mobile_number ship_name pier_name child_seat_required additional_services inbound_flight_terminal

    lists all additionally required fields when creating a booking for this location, can be empty if no fields are required. The field names correspond to the booking.fields.* entries in the settings endpoint which can be used for retrieving translated strings for these fields.

    location.parking_space_groups[].provider
    string Example: parku

    Choices: parku holidayextras inrix

    names the parking space provider. Additional information(terms and conditions, logo, …) about the provider can found be using the provider key from the field in settings

    location.parking_space_groups[].availability

    location.parking_space_groups[].availability.next_start
    string Example: 2016-...15:00:..

    the start of the next from now slot in which a parking space in this

    group is free and bookable, can be in the past

    location.parking_space_groups[].availability.next_end
    string Example: 2016-...15:00:..

    the end of the next slot from now in which a parking space in this group

    is free and bookable, can be in the past

    location.gates
    array 

    the gates connected to the location

    location.gates[].type
    string Example: qrcode

    Choices: qrcode beacon

    the type how the gate can be opened

    location.gates[].identifier
    string Example: PARKU3KU

    the identifier for the access method, a short identification string for qrcode and the bluetooth id for beacon

    location.gates[].gateways
    array 

    zone
    object 

    the zone that was booked, only available if type is onstreet.

    zone.id
    string Example: 101012

    the parking zone id

    zone.latitude
    number Example: 53.12341234

    latitude of the requested point

    zone.longitude
    number Example: 13.12341234

    longitude of the requested point

    zone.name
    string Example: Berlin 101012

    the parking space zone name

    zone.hours
    string Example: Mon-Fri, 08:00 - 22:30

    the translated availability time in this zone

    zone.price
    object (required) 

    information about the price for this zone

    zone.price.description
    string Example: 15 Min. gebührenfrei, danach 50 Cent pro 30 Min.

    description of the price

    zone.price.currency
    string Example: EUR

    Choices: EUR CHF

    the currency of the price

    zone.max_datetime_end
    string Example: 2009-06-30T18:30:00+02:00

    Latest time when a booking has to end. Bookings that are not stopped after this time will be automatically stopped on backend side.

    zone.duration_max_minutes`
    number Example: 760

    Maximum time the booking can be running in minutes. Bookings that are not stopped after this amount of time will be automatically stopped on backend side.

    extend
    object 

    extend.date_start
    string Example: 2016-10-27T10:00:00+0000

    start date of the extended booking

    extend.date_end
    string Example: 2016-10-27T12:00:00+0000

    end date of the extended booking

    extend.minutes
    number Example: 60

    length of extension in minutes

    extend.price
    number Example: 125

    price of the extension

    extend.currency
    string Example: EUR

    Choices: EUR CHF

    the currency of the price

    Create a new Booking ¶
    POST/bookings

    Request Attributes  (application/json)
    group_id
    string (required) Example: 00cd7cfd-e42d-11e2-8bf1-8a83f3373875

    The ID of the location you get returned from the locations request

    date_start
    string (required) Example: 2016-10-27T09:10:20+00:00

    start date and time of the booking

    date_end
    string (required) Example: 2016-10-27T10:10:20+00:00

    end date and time of the booking

    license_plate
    string (required) Example: B-AB 1234

    The license plate of the used car.

    Get all cars of a user from the cars request.

    phone_number
    string (required) Example: +493057701872

    The phone number.

    Get all phone numbers of a user from the phone_numbers request.

    payment
    array 

    The payments to use for paying (optional). This can be credits, coupons, paypal and braintree payments that have been authorized on the frontend.

    payment[].type
    string (required) Example: paypal

    Choices: paypal credit braintree

    The payment method.

    payment[].amount
    number (required) Example: 1200

    The amount to pay with this method as an integer where amount = 100 * decimal_amount.

    payment[].payload
    string (optional) Example: PAY-1CM399047K4649003KM4WJQQ

    The information of the payment provider to perform a payment. Required for paypal and braintree.

    The field provider_info should contain required payment information. Typically you just forward the info from your request to the payment provider into this field.

    • PayPal You can either use the complete PayPal response or just add the payment ID:

      payments.payload=PAY-1CM399047K4649003KM4WJQQ

    • Braintree There are two ways to pay with braintree:

      1. CreditCard-ID

        Retrieve the Card ID through the payment endpoint and add it to the request:

        payments.payload[id]=gphsyb

      2. CreditCard Credentials

        payments.payload[number]=EncryptedCreditCardNumber
payments.payload[expiration_date]=EncryptedExpirationDate
payments.payload[cvv]=EncryptedCvv
    payment_method
    object 

    The payment method to use for paying. This method will be used for paying the fee of the booking after all payments from the payments field have been applied. E.g. if you provided a 5 Euro voucher via payments, the payment method will be used on 5 Euro less than the actual booking fee.

    payment_method.id
    string (optional) Example: 1000bb3e-506d-11e5-9781-d43d7eece658

    the payment method id,

    only needed if type is immediate

    payment_method.type
    string (required) Example: immediate

    Choices: immediate

    How to execute the payment. Currently only immediate

    payments are supported.

    required_fields
    object 

    Parking space required fields defined in the locations request. The required fields should contain all required fields defined in location. All values should be sent as strings.

    required_fields.car_color
    string (optional) Example: red

    the car color

    required_fields.number_of_passengers
    string (optional) Example: 5

    the number of passengers

    user_metadata
    object 

    Additional information about a user (optional). This is for example latitude/longitude parameters for the users current position.

    user_metadata.latitude
    number (optional) Example: 52.521381

    users latitude

    user_metadata.longitude
    number (optional) Example: 13.3920158

    users longitude

    Example Request

    curl 'https://sandbox.test.parku.io/v5/bookings/005c4826-4e28-11e3-a675-d43d7eece53d' \
    --insecure \
    --user 012345678abcdef:parku
    Headers
    Authorization: Basic MDEyMzQ1Njc4YWJjZGVmOnBhcmt1

    price.transaction_fee
    number Example: 25

    the transaction fee included in amount

    price.payment_provider_fee
    number Example: 25

    the payment provider fee included in amount

    price.currency
    string Example: EUR

    Choices: EUR CHF

    the currency of the price

    violation
    object 

    violation.id
    string Example: 005c4826-4e28-11e3-a675-d43d7eece53d

    violation id

    status
    string Example: active

    status of the booking, can be active or canceled for offstreet bookings and running, finished or ‘canceled’ for onstreet bookings

    type
    string Example: offstreet

    Choices: offstreet onstreet

    the booking type

    group_id
    string Example: 123c4826-4e28-11e3-a675-d43d7eece53d

    the id of the booked parking space group

    parking_space_code
    string Example: ABCDE

    the code of the booked parking space

    location
    object 

    the location that was booked, only available if type is offstreet.

    location.id
    string Example: e644e4bc-4c5c-11e4-a24a-d43d7eecedd2

    unique identifier of the location used for referencing.

    location.address_slug
    string Example: dorfstrasse-11

    location.latitude
    number Example: 52.60826

    latitude part of the location geo coordinate

    location.longitude
    number Example: 13.19988

    longitude part of the location geo

    location.street
    string Example: Dorfstraße

    the street name of the location without number

    location.street_number
    string Example: 11

    the street number of the location

    location.postcode
    string Example: 16761

    post code of the location

    location.city
    string Example: Hennigsdorf

    city of the location

    location.country
    string Example: Deutschland

    country of the location in 2 character encoding country of the location in 2

    character encoding

    location.bookable
    boolean Example: true

    true if that locations can be booked via the parku API, false if the location

    is purely providing information

    location.payment
    object 

    available payment methods and types for the current user in this location. The payment methods and types depend on the private key of the logged in user. For locations requests using public keys these arrays will be empty.

    location.payment.methods
    array Example: [paypal]

    May Contain: paypal credits coupon braintree ideal

    Possible payment methods for this location and user

    location.payment.types
    array Example: [post]

    May Contain: post immediate

    Possible payment types for this location and user

    location.availability
    object 

    describes the availability of the location in relation to the request

    location.availability.current
    number Example: 0

    the number of parking spaces available in the group for the requested time period defined

    by start and endthe number of parking spaces available in the group for the requested time period defined by start and end

    location.availability.maximum
    number Example: 1

    the overall number of parking spaces at this group the overall number of parking spaces at

    this group

    location.availability.next_start
    string Example: 2016-...15:00:..

    the start of the next from now slot in which a parking space in this

    group is free and bookable, can be in the past

    location.availability.next_end
    string Example: 2016-...15:00:..

    the end of the next slot from now in which a parking space in this group

    is free and bookable, can be in the past

    location.parking_space_groups
    array 

    different parking space groups for this location. See Parking Space Group Data

    location.parking_space_groups[].id
    string Example: 1644c5dc-4c5c-11e4-a24a-d43d7eecedd2

    unique identifier of the location used for referencing.

    location.parking_space_groups[].type
    string Example: off-street

    Choices: off-street park-and-ride professional-garage airport-parking harbor-parking

    describes the type of location and can be one of the following.

    location.parking_space_groups[].description
    string Example: Doppelparkplatz. Jedoch nur für ein Auto zu vermieten.

    location.parking_space_groups[].image_urls
    array Example: [https://parku.de/images/parkingspace/020a81f5-c8b9-11e4-bfd2-d43d7eece658/640x286.jpg]

    urls of location images, can be empty

    location.parking_space_groups[].options
    array Example: [excess length]

    May Contain: excess length indoor disabled patio barrier charging station key_necessary long_term_booking surveillance valet_service

    describes which options are available at the location and can contains each of the following elements. The list can be empty.

    location.parking_space_groups[].support
    object 

    location.parking_space_groups[].support.phone_number
    string Example: +493012064329

    returns the support center phone number for this location

    location.parking_space_groups[].price
    object 

    location.parking_space_groups[].price.total
    number Example: 150

    the total price for booking a parking space of this group if start and end was provided, null otherwise.

    location.parking_space_groups[].price.currency
    string Example: EUR

    Choices: EUR CHF

    the currency of the price

    location.parking_space_groups[].price.period
    string Example: timeframe

    Choices: timeframe day week month

    contains the period for how long the price is valid, can be null if start or end was not provided

    location.parking_space_groups[].price.rate_hourly
    number Example: 10

    shows the price for per hour

    location.parking_space_groups[].price.rate_daily
    number Example: 100

    shows the price per day

    location.parking_space_groups[].price.rate_weekly
    number Example: 300

    shows the price per week

    location.parking_space_groups[].price.rate_monthly
    number Example: 1500

    shows the price per month

    location.parking_space_groups[].user_owned
    boolean Example: false

    true if the user who requested the location is also the owner of the parking space. This allows to determine if the user could block the parking space from bookings.

    location.parking_space_groups[].settings
    object 

    provides booking requirements for the location. The settings of a location are used in favor of the global settings that can be found in the settings endpoint.

    location.parking_space_groups[].settings.bookable_range_start
    number Example: -15

    start of the range wherein a booking is allowed in minutes from now.

    location.parking_space_groups[].settings.bookable_range_end
    number Example: 43200

    end of the range wherein a booking is allowed in minutes from now. end of the range wherein a booking is allowed in minutes from now.

    location.parking_space_groups[].settings.booking_duration_min
    number Example: 30

    minimum duration of a booking in minutes.

    location.parking_space_groups[].settings.booking_duration_max
    number Example: 43200

    maximum duration of a booking in minutes.

    location.parking_space_groups[].required_fields
    array Example: [car_registration_number]

    May Contain: car_registration_number car_make car_model car_colour number_of_passengers car_dropoff_time car_pickup_time outbound_flight_terminal outbound_flight_number inbound_flight_number outbound_flight_time inbound_flight_time user_mobile_number ship_name pier_name child_seat_required additional_services inbound_flight_terminal

    lists all additionally required fields when creating a booking for this location, can be empty if no fields are required. The field names correspond to the booking.fields.* entries in the settings endpoint which can be used for retrieving translated strings for these fields.

    location.parking_space_groups[].provider
    string Example: parku

    Choices: parku holidayextras inrix

    names the parking space provider. Additional information(terms and conditions, logo, …) about the provider can found be using the provider key from the field in settings

    location.parking_space_groups[].availability
    object 

    describes the availability of the group in relation to the requestdescribes the

    availability of the group in relation to the request

    location.parking_space_groups[].availability.current

    by start and endthe number of parking spaces available in the group for the requested time period defined by start and end

    number Example: 1

    string Example: 2016-...15:00:..

    location.parking_space_groups[].availability.next_end
    string Example: 2016-...15:00:..

    the end of the next slot from now in which a parking space in this group

    is free and bookable, can be in the past

    location.gates
    array 

    the gates connected to the location

    location.gates[].type
    string Example: qrcode

    Choices: qrcode beacon

    the type how the gate can be opened

    location.gates[].identifier
    string Example: PARKU3KU

    the identifier for the access method, a short identification string for qrcode and the bluetooth id for beacon

    location.gates[].gateways
    array 

    zone
    object 

    the zone that was booked, only available if type is onstreet.

    zone.id
    string Example: 101012

    the parking zone id

    zone.latitude
    number Example: 53.12341234

    latitude of the requested point

    zone.longitude
    number Example: 13.12341234

    longitude of the requested point

    zone.name
    string Example: Berlin 101012

    the parking space zone name

    zone.hours
    string Example: Mon-Fri, 08:00 - 22:30

    the translated availability time in this zone

    zone.price
    object (required) 

    information about the price for this zone

    zone.price.description
    string Example: 15 Min. gebührenfrei, danach 50 Cent pro 30 Min.

    description of the price

    zone.price.currency
    string Example: EUR

    Choices: EUR CHF

    the currency of the price

    zone.max_datetime_end
    string Example: 2009-06-30T18:30:00+02:00

    Latest time when a booking has to end. Bookings that are not stopped after this time will be automatically stopped on backend side.

    zone.duration_max_minutes`
    number Example: 760

    Maximum time the booking can be running in minutes. Bookings that are not stopped after this amount of time will be automatically stopped on backend side.

    extend
    object 

    extend.date_start
    string Example: 2016-10-27T10:00:00+0000

    start date of the extended booking

    extend.date_end
    string Example: 2016-10-27T12:00:00+0000

    end date of the extended booking

    extend.minutes
    number Example: 60

    length of extension in minutes

    extend.price
    number Example: 125

    Retrieve a Booking ¶
    GET/bookings/{reference}

    Retrieves the details of an existing booking. You need to supply either the id or the reference of a booking.

    URI Parameters
    reference
    string (required) Example: 005c4826-4e28-11e3-a675-d43d7eece53d

    The id or code of the booking

    Example Request

    curl 'https://sandbox.test.parku.io/v5/bookings/00cd7cfd-e42d-11e2-8bf1-8a83f3373875' \
    --insecure \
    --request PUT \
    --user 012345678abcdef:parku \
    -H 'Content-Type: application/json' \
    -d @- << EOF
    {

            ],

          },
          "amount": {
            "type": "number",
            "description": "The amount to pay with this method as an integer where `amount = 100 * decimal_amount`."
          },
          "payload": {
            "type": "string",
            "description": "The information of the payment provider to perform a payment.  Required for `paypal` and `braintree`.\n\nThe field `provider_info` should contain required payment information.\nTypically you just forward the info from your request to the payment provider into this field.\n\n* **PayPal**\n    You can either use the complete PayPal response or just add the payment ID:\n    ```\n    payments.payload=PAY-1CM399047K4649003KM4WJQQ\n    ```\n\n* **Braintree**\n    There are two ways to pay with braintree:\n    1. _CreditCard-ID_\n\n        Retrieve the Card ID through the payment endpoint and add it to the request:\n\n        ```\n        payments.payload[id]=gphsyb\n        ```\n    2. _CreditCard Credentials_\n\n        ```\n        payments.payload[number]=EncryptedCreditCardNumber\n        payments.payload[expiration_date]=EncryptedExpirationDate\n        payments.payload[cvv]=EncryptedCvv\n        ```"
          }
        },
        "required": [
          "type",
          "amount"
        ]

    location.bookable
    boolean Example: true

    true if that locations can be booked via the parku API, false if the location

    is purely providing information

    location.payment
    object 

    available payment methods and types for the current user in this location. The payment methods and types depend on the private key of the logged in user. For locations requests using public keys these arrays will be empty.

    location.payment.methods
    array Example: [paypal]

    May Contain: paypal credits coupon braintree ideal

    Possible payment methods for this location and user

    location.payment.types
    array Example: [post]

    May Contain: post immediate

    Possible payment types for this location and user

    location.availability

    location.availability.current

    the number of parking spaces available in the group for the requested time period defined

    by start and endthe number of parking spaces available in the group for the requested time period defined by start and end

    location.availability.maximum

    location.availability.next_start
    string Example: 2016-...15:00:..

    the start of the next from now slot in which a parking space in this

    group is free and bookable, can be in the past

    location.availability.next_end
    string Example: 2016-...15:00:..

    the end of the next slot from now in which a parking space in this group

    is free and bookable, can be in the past

    location.parking_space_groups
    array 

    different parking space groups for this location. See Parking Space Group Data

    location.parking_space_groups[].id
    string Example: 1644c5dc-4c5c-11e4-a24a-d43d7eecedd2

    unique identifier of the location used for referencing.

    location.parking_space_groups[].type
    string Example: off-street

    Choices: off-street park-and-ride professional-garage airport-parking harbor-parking

    describes the type of location and can be one of the following.

    location.parking_space_groups[].description
    string Example: Doppelparkplatz. Jedoch nur für ein Auto zu vermieten.

    location.parking_space_groups[].image_urls
    array Example: [https://parku.de/images/parkingspace/020a81f5-c8b9-11e4-bfd2-d43d7eece658/640x286.jpg]

    urls of location images, can be empty

    location.parking_space_groups[].options
    array Example: [excess length]

    May Contain: excess length indoor disabled patio barrier charging station key_necessary long_term_booking surveillance valet_service

    describes which options are available at the location and can contains each of the following elements. The list can be empty.

    location.parking_space_groups[].support

    location.parking_space_groups[].support.phone_number
    string Example: +493012064329

    location.parking_space_groups[].price
    object 

    location.parking_space_groups[].price.total
    number Example: 150

    the total price for booking a parking space of this group if start and end was provided, null otherwise.

    location.parking_space_groups[].price.currency
    string Example: EUR

    Choices: EUR CHF

    the currency of the price

    location.parking_space_groups[].price.period
    string Example: timeframe

    Choices: timeframe day week month

    contains the period for how long the price is valid, can be null if start or end was not provided

    location.parking_space_groups[].price.rate_hourly
    number Example: 10

    shows the price for per hour

    location.parking_space_groups[].price.rate_daily
    number Example: 100

    shows the price per day

    location.parking_space_groups[].price.rate_weekly
    number Example: 300

    shows the price per week

    location.parking_space_groups[].price.rate_monthly
    number Example: 1500

    shows the price per month

    location.parking_space_groups[].user_owned
    boolean Example: false

    true if the user who requested the location is also the owner of the parking space. This allows to determine if the user could block the parking space from bookings.

    location.parking_space_groups[].settings
    object 

    provides booking requirements for the location. The settings of a location are used in favor of the global settings that can be found in the settings endpoint.

    location.parking_space_groups[].settings.bookable_range_start
    number Example: -15

    start of the range wherein a booking is allowed in minutes from now.

    location.parking_space_groups[].settings.bookable_range_end
    number Example: 43200

    end of the range wherein a booking is allowed in minutes from now. end of the range wherein a booking is allowed in minutes from now.

    location.parking_space_groups[].settings.booking_duration_min
    number Example: 30

    minimum duration of a booking in minutes.

    location.parking_space_groups[].settings.booking_duration_max
    number Example: 43200

    maximum duration of a booking in minutes.

    location.parking_space_groups[].required_fields
    array Example: [car_registration_number]

    May Contain: car_registration_number car_make car_model car_colour number_of_passengers car_dropoff_time car_pickup_time outbound_flight_terminal outbound_flight_number inbound_flight_number outbound_flight_time inbound_flight_time user_mobile_number ship_name pier_name child_seat_required additional_services inbound_flight_terminal

    lists all additionally required fields when creating a booking for this location, can be empty if no fields are required. The field names correspond to the booking.fields.* entries in the settings endpoint which can be used for retrieving translated strings for these fields.

    location.parking_space_groups[].provider
    string Example: parku

    Choices: parku holidayextras inrix

    names the parking space provider. Additional information(terms and conditions, logo, …) about the provider can found be using the provider key from the field in settings

    zone.hours
    string Example: Mon-Fri, 08:00 - 22:30

    object (required)

    zone.price.description
    string Example: 15 Min. gebührenfrei, danach 50 Cent pro 30 Min.

    description of the price

    zone.price.currency
    string Example: EUR

    Choices: EUR CHF

    the currency of the price

    zone.max_datetime_end
    string Example: 2009-06-30T18:30:00+02:00

    Latest time when a booking has to end. Bookings that are not stopped after this time will be automatically stopped on backend side.

    zone.duration_max_minutes`
    number Example: 760

    Maximum time the booking can be running in minutes. Bookings that are not stopped after this amount of time will be automatically stopped on backend side.

    Update a Booking ¶
    PUT/bookings/{booking_id}

    Updates the booking by setting the values of the parameters passed. Any parameter not provided will be left unchanged.

    Request Attributes  (application/json)
    license_plate
    string (optional) Example: B-BC 4567

    refer to the description of Create a new Booking

    phone_number
    string (optional) Example: +493057701871

    refer to the description of Create a new Booking

    date_end
    string (optional) Example: 2016-10-27T17:00:00+0000

    refer to the description of Create a new Booking

    payment
    array 

    The payments to use for paying (optional). This can be credits, coupons, paypal and braintree payments that have been authorized on the frontend.

    payment[].type
    string (required) Example: paypal

    Choices: paypal credit braintree

    The payment method.

    payment[].amount
    number (required) Example: 1200

    The amount to pay with this method as an integer where amount = 100 * decimal_amount.

    payment[].payload
    string (optional) Example: PAY-1CM399047K4649003KM4WJQQ

    The information of the payment provider to perform a payment. Required for paypal and braintree.

    The field provider_info should contain required payment information. Typically you just forward the info from your request to the payment provider into this field.

    • PayPal You can either use the complete PayPal response or just add the payment ID:

      payments.payload=PAY-1CM399047K4649003KM4WJQQ

    • Braintree There are two ways to pay with braintree:

      1. CreditCard-ID

        Retrieve the Card ID through the payment endpoint and add it to the request:

        payments.payload[id]=gphsyb

      2. CreditCard Credentials

        payments.payload[number]=EncryptedCreditCardNumber
payments.payload[expiration_date]=EncryptedExpirationDate
payments.payload[cvv]=EncryptedCvv
    payment_method
    object 

    The payment method to use for paying.

    payment_method.id
    string (optional) Example: 1000bb3e-506d-11e5-9781-d43d7eece658

    the payment method id,

    only needed if type is immediate

    payment_method.type
    string (required) Example: immediate

    Choices: immediate

    How to execute the payment. Currently only immediate

    payments are supported.

    URI Parameters
    booking_id
    string (required) Example: 00cd7cfd-e42d-11e2-8bf1-8a83f3373875

    the booking id

    Example Request

    curl 'https://sandbox.test.parku.io/v5/bookings/00cd7cfd-e42d-11e2-8bf1-8a83f3373875' \
    --insecure \
    --request DELETE \
    --user 012345678abcdef:parku
    Headers
    Authorization: Basic MDEyMzQ1Njc4YWJjZGVmOnBhcmt1

    Example Response

    200

    zone.max_datetime_end
    string Example: 2009-06-30T18:30:00+02:00

    Latest time when a booking has to end. Bookings that are not stopped after this time will be automatically stopped on backend side.

    zone.duration_max_minutes`
    number Example: 760

    Maximum time the booking can be running in minutes. Bookings that are not stopped after this amount of time will be automatically stopped on backend side.

    extend
    object 

    extend.date_start
    string Example: 2016-10-27T10:00:00+0000

    start date of the extended booking

    extend.date_end
    string Example: 2016-10-27T12:00:00+0000

    end date of the extended booking

    extend.minutes
    number Example: 60

    length of extension in minutes

    extend.price
    number Example: 125

    price of the extension

    extend.currency
    string Example: EUR

    Choices: EUR CHF

    the currency of the price

    Cancel a Booking ¶
    DELETE/bookings/{booking_id}

    URI Parameters
    booking_id
    string (required) Example: 00cd7cfd-e42d-11e2-8bf1-8a83f3373875

    the booking id

    Example Request

    curl 'https://sandbox.test.parku.io/v5/bookings?count=3&offset=10&status=active&type=all' \
    --insecure \
    --user 012345678abcdef:parku
    Headers
    Authorization: Basic MDEyMzQ1Njc4YWJjZGVmOnBhcmt1

    May Contain: excess length indoor disabled patio barrier charging station key_necessary long_term_booking surveillance valet_service

    describes which options are available at the location and can contains each of the following elements. The list can be empty.

    .[].location.parking_space_groups[].support
    object 

    .[].location.parking_space_groups[].price
    object 

    .[].location.parking_space_groups[].user_owned
    boolean Example: false

    true if the user who requested the location is also the owner of the parking space. This allows to determine if the user could block the parking space from bookings.

    .[].location.parking_space_groups[].settings
    object 

    provides booking requirements for the location. The settings of a location are used in favor of the global settings that can be found in the settings endpoint.

    .[].location.parking_space_groups[].required_fields
    array Example: [car_registration_number]

    May Contain: car_registration_number car_make car_model car_colour number_of_passengers car_dropoff_time car_pickup_time outbound_flight_terminal outbound_flight_number inbound_flight_number outbound_flight_time inbound_flight_time user_mobile_number ship_name pier_name child_seat_required additional_services inbound_flight_terminal

    lists all additionally required fields when creating a booking for this location, can be empty if no fields are required. The field names correspond to the booking.fields.* entries in the settings endpoint which can be used for retrieving translated strings for these fields.

    .[].location.parking_space_groups[].provider
    string Example: parku

    Choices: parku holidayextras inrix

    names the parking space provider. Additional information(terms and conditions, logo, …) about the provider can found be using the provider key from the field in settings

    .[].location.parking_space_groups[].availability
    object 

    describes the availability of the group in relation to the requestdescribes the

    availability of the group in relation to the request

    .[].location.gates
    array 

    the gates connected to the location

    .[].location.gates[].type
    string Example: qrcode

    Choices: qrcode beacon

    the type how the gate can be opened

    .[].location.gates[].identifier
    string Example: PARKU3KU

    the identifier for the access method, a short identification string for qrcode and the bluetooth id for beacon

    .[].location.gates[].gateways
    array 

    .[].zone
    object 

    the zone that was booked, only available if type is onstreet.

    .[].zone.id
    string Example: 101012

    the parking zone id

    .[].zone.latitude
    number Example: 53.12341234

    latitude of the requested point

    .[].zone.longitude
    number Example: 13.12341234

    longitude of the requested point

    .[].zone.name
    string Example: Berlin 101012

    the parking space zone name

    .[].zone.hours
    string Example: Mon-Fri, 08:00 - 22:30

    the translated availability time in this zone

    .[].zone.price
    object (required) 

    information about the price for this zone

    .[].zone.price.description
    string Example: 15 Min. gebührenfrei, danach 50 Cent pro 30 Min.

    description of the price

    .[].zone.price.currency
    string Example: EUR

    Choices: EUR CHF

    the currency of the price

    .[].zone.max_datetime_end
    string Example: 2009-06-30T18:30:00+02:00

    Latest time when a booking has to end. Bookings that are not stopped after this time will be automatically stopped on backend side.

    .[].zone.duration_max_minutes`
    number Example: 760

    Maximum time the booking can be running in minutes. Bookings that are not stopped after this amount of time will be automatically stopped on backend side.

    .[].extend
    object 

    .[].extend.date_start
    string Example: 2016-10-27T10:00:00+0000

    start date of the extended booking

    .[].extend.date_end
    string Example: 2016-10-27T12:00:00+0000

    end date of the extended booking

    .[].extend.minutes
    number Example: 60

    length of extension in minutes

    .[].extend.price
    number Example: 125

    price of the extension

    .[].extend.currency
    string Example: EUR

    Choices: EUR CHF

    the currency of the price

    List bookings ¶
    GET/bookings{?count,offset,status,type}

    URI Parameters
    count
    number (optional) Default: 10 Example: 3

    A limit on the number of objects to be returned. Count can range between 1 and 100 items.

    offset
    number (optional) Default: 0 Example: 10

    An offset into the list of returned items. The API will return the requested number of items starting at that offset.

    status
    enum (optional) Default: all Example: active

    Filter bookings for status.

    Choices: all active cancelled running finished

    type
    enum (optional) Default: all Example: all

    Filter bookings for their type

    Choices: all offstreet onstreet

    Example Request

    curl 'https://sandbox.test.parku.io/v5/bookings/00cd7cfd-e42d-11e2-8bf1-8a83f3373875/stop' \
    --insecure \
    --request POST \
    --user 012345678abcdef:parku
    Headers
    Content-Type: application/json
    Authorization: Basic MDEyMzQ1Njc4YWJjZGVmOnBhcmt1

    group_id
    string Example: 123c4826-4e28-11e3-a675-d43d7eece53d

    the id of the booked parking space group

    parking_space_code
    string Example: ABCDE

    the code of the booked parking space

    location
    object 

    the location that was booked, only available if type is offstreet.

    location.id
    string Example: e644e4bc-4c5c-11e4-a24a-d43d7eecedd2

    unique identifier of the location used for referencing.

    location.address_slug
    string Example: dorfstrasse-11

    location.latitude
    number Example: 52.60826

    latitude part of the location geo coordinate

    location.longitude
    number Example: 13.19988

    longitude part of the location geo

    location.street
    string Example: Dorfstraße

    the street name of the location without number

    location.street_number
    string Example: 11

    the street number of the location

    location.postcode
    string Example: 16761

    post code of the location

    location.city
    string Example: Hennigsdorf

    city of the location

    location.country
    string Example: Deutschland

    country of the location in 2 character encoding country of the location in 2

    character encoding

    location.bookable
    boolean Example: true

    true if that locations can be booked via the parku API, false if the location

    is purely providing information

    location.payment
    object 

    available payment methods and types for the current user in this location. The payment methods and types depend on the private key of the logged in user. For locations requests using public keys these arrays will be empty.

    location.payment.methods
    array Example: [paypal]

    May Contain: paypal credits coupon braintree ideal

    Possible payment methods for this location and user

    location.payment.types
    array Example: [post]

    May Contain: post immediate

    Possible payment types for this location and user

    location.availability
    object 

    describes the availability of the location in relation to the request

    location.availability.current
    number Example: 0

    the number of parking spaces available in the group for the requested time period defined

    by start and endthe number of parking spaces available in the group for the requested time period defined by start and end

    location.availability.maximum
    number Example: 1

    the overall number of parking spaces at this group the overall number of parking spaces at

    this group

    location.availability.next_start
    string Example: 2016-...15:00:..

    the start of the next from now slot in which a parking space in this

    group is free and bookable, can be in the past

    location.availability.next_end
    string Example: 2016-...15:00:..

    the end of the next slot from now in which a parking space in this group

    is free and bookable, can be in the past

    location.parking_space_groups
    array 

    different parking space groups for this location. See Parking Space Group Data

    location.parking_space_groups[].id
    string Example: 1644c5dc-4c5c-11e4-a24a-d43d7eecedd2

    unique identifier of the location used for referencing.

    location.parking_space_groups[].type
    string Example: off-street

    Choices: off-street park-and-ride professional-garage airport-parking harbor-parking

    describes the type of location and can be one of the following.

    location.parking_space_groups[].description
    string Example: Doppelparkplatz. Jedoch nur für ein Auto zu vermieten.

    location.parking_space_groups[].image_urls
    array Example: [https://parku.de/images/parkingspace/020a81f5-c8b9-11e4-bfd2-d43d7eece658/640x286.jpg]

    urls of location images, can be empty

    location.parking_space_groups[].options
    array Example: [excess length]

    May Contain: excess length indoor disabled patio barrier charging station key_necessary long_term_booking surveillance valet_service

    describes which options are available at the location and can contains each of the following elements. The list can be empty.

    location.parking_space_groups[].support
    object 

    location.parking_space_groups[].support.phone_number
    string Example: +493012064329

    returns the support center phone number for this location

    location.parking_space_groups[].price
    object 

    location.parking_space_groups[].price.total
    number Example: 150

    the total price for booking a parking space of this group if start and end was provided, null otherwise.

    location.parking_space_groups[].price.currency
    string Example: EUR

    Choices: EUR CHF

    the currency of the price

    location.parking_space_groups[].price.period
    string Example: timeframe

    Choices: timeframe day week month

    contains the period for how long the price is valid, can be null if start or end was not provided

    location.parking_space_groups[].price.rate_hourly
    number Example: 10

    shows the price for per hour

    location.parking_space_groups[].price.rate_daily
    number Example: 100

    shows the price per day

    location.parking_space_groups[].price.rate_weekly
    number Example: 300

    shows the price per week

    location.parking_space_groups[].price.rate_monthly
    number Example: 1500

    shows the price per month

    location.parking_space_groups[].user_owned
    boolean Example: false

    true if the user who requested the location is also the owner of the parking space. This allows to determine if the user could block the parking space from bookings.

    location.parking_space_groups[].settings
    object 

    provides booking requirements for the location. The settings of a location are used in favor of the global settings that can be found in the settings endpoint.

    location.parking_space_groups[].settings.bookable_range_start
    number Example: -15

    start of the range wherein a booking is allowed in minutes from now.

    location.parking_space_groups[].settings.bookable_range_end
    number Example: 43200

    end of the range wherein a booking is allowed in minutes from now. end of the range wherein a booking is allowed in minutes from now.

    location.parking_space_groups[].settings.booking_duration_min
    number Example: 30

    minimum duration of a booking in minutes.

    location.parking_space_groups[].settings.booking_duration_max
    number Example: 43200

    maximum duration of a booking in minutes.

    location.parking_space_groups[].required_fields
    array Example: [car_registration_number]

    May Contain: car_registration_number car_make car_model car_colour number_of_passengers car_dropoff_time car_pickup_time outbound_flight_terminal outbound_flight_number inbound_flight_number outbound_flight_time inbound_flight_time user_mobile_number ship_name pier_name child_seat_required additional_services inbound_flight_terminal

    lists all additionally required fields when creating a booking for this location, can be empty if no fields are required. The field names correspond to the booking.fields.* entries in the settings endpoint which can be used for retrieving translated strings for these fields.

    location.parking_space_groups[].provider
    string Example: parku

    Choices: parku holidayextras inrix

    names the parking space provider. Additional information(terms and conditions, logo, …) about the provider can found be using the provider key from the field in settings

    location.parking_space_groups[].availability
    object 

    describes the availability of the group in relation to the requestdescribes the

    location.gates

    the gates connected to the location

    string Example: qrcode

    Choices: qrcode beacon

    the type how the gate can be opened

    location.gates[].identifier
    string Example: PARKU3KU

    the identifier for the access method, a short identification string for qrcode and the bluetooth id for beacon

    location.gates[].gateways
    array 

    zone
    object 

    the zone that was booked, only available if type is onstreet.

    zone.id
    string Example: 101012

    the parking zone id

    zone.latitude
    number Example: 53.12341234

    latitude of the requested point

    zone.longitude
    number Example: 13.12341234

    longitude of the requested point

    zone.name
    string Example: Berlin 101012

    the parking space zone name

    zone.hours
    string Example: Mon-Fri, 08:00 - 22:30

    the translated availability time in this zone

    zone.price
    object (required) 

    information about the price for this zone

    zone.price.description
    string Example: 15 Min. gebührenfrei, danach 50 Cent pro 30 Min.

    description of the price

    zone.price.currency
    string Example: EUR

    Choices: EUR CHF

    the currency of the price

    zone.max_datetime_end
    string Example: 2009-06-30T18:30:00+02:00

    Latest time when a booking has to end. Bookings that are not stopped after this time will be automatically stopped on backend side.

    zone.duration_max_minutes`
    number Example: 760

    Maximum time the booking can be running in minutes. Bookings that are not stopped after this amount of time will be automatically stopped on backend side.

    object

    string Example: 2016-10-27T10:00:00+0000

    extend.date_end

    extend.price

    Stop a Booking ¶
    POST/bookings/{booking_id}/stop

    Stops and pays a booking.

    Currently supports stopping onstreet bookings only.

    List all cars ¶
    GET/cars

    Returns a list of all cars of the user. The cars are returned sorted by creation date, with the most recently created car appearing first.

    Example Request

    curl 'https://sandbox.test.parku.io/v5/cars' \
    --insecure \
    --request POST \
    --user 012345678abcdef:parku \
    -H 'Content-Type: application/json' \
    -d @- << EOF
    {
      "license_plate": "B-AB 1234",
      "vehicle": "Isetta",
      "country": "DE"
    }
    EOF
    Headers
    Content-Type: application/json
    Authorization: Basic MDEyMzQ1Njc4YWJjZGVmOnBhcmt1
    Body
    {
  "license_plate": "B-AB 1234",
  "vehicle": "Isetta",
  "country": "DE"
}
    Schema
    {
  "type": "object",
  "properties": {
    "license_plate": {
      "type": "string",
      "description": "The license plate for the stored car."
    },
    "vehicle": {
      "type": "string",
      "description": "A name for the car to be identified easier."
    },
    "country": {
      "enum": [
        "DE",
        "CH"
      ],
      "description": "The country code the license plate."
    }
  },
  "required": [
    "license_plate"
  ],
  "$schema": "http://json-schema.org/draft-04/schema#"
}

    Example Response

    201
    Headers
    Content-Type: application/json
    Body
    {
  "id": 23,
  "license_plate": "B-AB 1234",
  "vehicle": "Isetta",
  "country": "DE"
}

    Coupon ¶

    Coupon ¶

    Access needs a private key.

    Example Request

    curl 'https://sandbox.test.parku.io/v5/coupon/Zm9vYmFyMTIz?action=test&amount=42' \
    --insecure \
    --user 012345678abcdef:parku
    Headers
    Authorization: Basic MDEyMzQ1Njc4YWJjZGVmOnBhcmt1

    Example Response

    200422404
    code string Decoded, sanitized coupon code
    value number Coupons value
    deduction number Amount used of coupon value
    Headers
    Content-Type: application/json
    Body
    {
  "code": "foobar123",
  "value": 10,
  "deduction": 10
}
    Code Description
    10 “amount” is faulty, probably below 0.
    30 Coupon quota exhausted.
    31 User usage quota for this coupon is exhausted.
    32 User usage quota for a coupon is same grouping is exhausted.
    40 Platform (Android, iOS, web) is not enabled. Some coupons only work on specific a platform.
    Headers
    Content-Type: application/json
    Body
    {
  "error": [
    {
      "code": 31,
      "message": "Coupon usage exceeded."
    }
  ]
}
    Code Description
    20 Coupon not found.
    21 Coupon is inactive.
    22 Coupon expired.
    23 Coupon date (start or end) prohibit coupon usage.
    Headers
    Content-Type: application/json
    Body
    {
  "error": [
    {
      "code": 20,
      "message": "Coupon not found."
    }
  ]
}

    Devices ¶

    Access needs a private key.

    Devices ¶

    This endpoint is used to send the latest device identifier to the backend. The device identifier is used to send push notifications.

    Only the creation of identifiers is allowed. Retrieving is not allowed.

    Example Request

    curl 'https://sandbox.test.parku.io/v5/devices' \
    --insecure \
    --request POST \
    --user 012345678abcdef:parku \
    -H 'Content-Type: application/json' \
    -d @- << EOF
    {
      "ios_device_token": "A339F8BE4F...",
      "android_registration_id": "A339F8BE4F..."
    }
    EOF
    Headers
    Content-Type: application/json
    Authorization: Basic MDEyMzQ1Njc4YWJjZGVmOnBhcmt1
    Body
    {
  "ios_device_token": "A339F8BE4F...",
  "android_registration_id": "A339F8BE4F..."
}
    Schema
    {
  "type": "object",
  "properties": {
    "ios_device_token": {
      "type": "string",
      "description": "iOS push notification identifier via APNs.\n\nFull integration and how to request a push notification Device Token through Apple's APM service is accessible\n[here](https://developer.apple.com/library/content/documentation/NetworkingInternet/Conceptual/RemoteNotificationsPG/APNSOverview.html).\nDevice Token may be raw format or in push format."
    },
    "android_registration_id": {
      "type": "string",
      "description": "Android push notification identifier via GCM.\n\nFull integration and how to request a push notification Registration ID through Android's GCM service is\naccessible [here](http://developer.android.com/google/gcm/gs.html)."
    }
  },
  "$schema": "http://json-schema.org/draft-04/schema#"
}

    Example Response

    204
    This response has no content.

    Create an Identifier ¶
    POST/devices

    Send the latest device identifier to the backend.

    The iOS device token can change through time. Apple suggests to send the device token every time the app launches.

    Request Attributes  (application/json)
    ios_device_token
    string (optional) Example: A339F8BE4F...

    iOS push notification identifier via APNs.

    Full integration and how to request a push notification Device Token through Apple’s APM service is accessible here. Device Token may be raw format or in push format.

    android_registration_id
    string (optional) Example: A339F8BE4F...

    Android push notification identifier via GCM.

    Full integration and how to request a push notification Registration ID through Android’s GCM service is accessible here.

    Errors ¶

    Status: 422 Unprocessable Entity
    {
  "error": {
      "code": "email",
      "message": "Booking failed."
    }

}

    parku uses conventional HTTP response codes to indicate success or failure of an API request. In general, codes in the 2xx range indicate success, codes in the 4xx range indicate an error that resulted from the provided information (e.g. a required parameter was missing, etc.), and codes in the 5xx range indicate an error with parku’s servers.

    HTTP Status Codes Summary ¶

    Code Description
    200 OK - Everything worked as expected.
    201 Created - Item was created successfully. The URL to the item can be found in the “Location”-Header.
    204 No Content - The request was successful.
    401 Unauthorized - No valid API key provided.
    404 Not Found - The requested item doesn’t exist.
    422 Unprocessable Entity
    5xx Server errors - something went wrong on parku’s end.

    All error objects have field properties so that your client can tell what the problem is. There is also an error message to let you know what is wrong with the field.

    Facebook Login ¶
    POST/facebook/login

    When a new user was created through Facebook, the country is not set. In this case, you must ask the user for the country and update the user profile accordingly.

    All further requests using the token as HTTP Basic Auth username are made on behalf of the user.

    string (required) Example: 1234...

    The access token which is used to obtain information from Facebook.

    The token must have the permissions to get the users email.

    Locations ¶

    Access needs at least a public key.

    Locations ¶

    The location model contains the directly location related information (e.g. street and city) as well as one or more parking space groups.

    A parking space group is a group of parking spaces with similar properties. Bookings are made using parking space group ids.

    The location list can cover a large number of locations in its response. In order to keep the responses reasonably fast and small that request will return a mix of locations and clusters. A location cluster contains information about how many locations are in a certain area.

    Locations and Clusters Model Example
    {

    {

      "type": "postcode",

    Locations and Clusters Model ¶

    clusters
    array 

    A cluster contains meta information about the locations inside a specific area. The cluster itself contains 2 levels. The first level groups the second level clusters that are given by the field includes.

    First level clusters are great for display on maps as we make sure that those clusters have a certain distance to each other.

    Second level clusters are great for being displayed in a list as they all have a distinct name and a parent city/country that can be used for grouping them. These clusters work on 3 predefined levels: - postcode: contains only locations with same postcode - city: contains only locations in same city - country: contains only locations in same country Which level is returned depends on the bounding box size of your request.

    locations
    array 

    First Level Cluster Model Example
    {
  "title": "13405",
  "type": "postcode",
  "count": 4,
  "center_latitude": 52.528809357143,
  "center_longitude": 13.379654547619,
  "sw_latitude": 52.505681,
  "sw_longitude": 13.285105,
  "ne_latitude": 52.576979,
  "ne_longitude": 13.47168,
  "includes": [
    {
      "title": "10115",
      "type": "postcode",
      "count": 4,
      "center_latitude": 52.528809357143,
      "center_longitude": 13.379654547619,
      "sw_latitude": 52.505681,
      "sw_longitude": 13.285105,
      "ne_latitude": 52.576979,
      "ne_longitude": 13.47168,
      "city": "Berlin",
      "country": "Deutschland"
    }
  ]
}

    First Level Cluster Model ¶

    title
    string (optional) Example: 13405

    type
    string (optional) Example: postcode

    Choices: postcode city country

    count
    number (optional) Example: 4

    The number of locations inside the cluster.

    center_latitude
    number (optional) Example: 52.528809357143

    Latitude of the cluster center.

    center_longitude
    number (optional) Example: 13.379654547619

    Longitude of the cluster center.

    sw_latitude
    number (optional) Example: 52.505681

    South west corner latitude of the cluster bounding boxes.

    sw_longitude
    number (optional) Example: 13.285105

    South west corner longitude of the cluster bounding boxes.

    ne_latitude
    number (optional) Example: 52.576979

    North east corner latitude of the cluster bounding boxes.

    ne_longitude
    number (optional) Example: 13.47168

    North east corner longitude of the cluster bounding boxes.

    includes
    array 

    List of second level clusters contained in this cluster.

    Second Level Cluster Model Example
    {
  "title": "10115",
  "type": "postcode",
  "count": 4,
  "center_latitude": 52.528809357143,
  "center_longitude": 13.379654547619,
  "sw_latitude": 52.505681,
  "sw_longitude": 13.285105,
  "ne_latitude": 52.576979,
  "ne_longitude": 13.47168,
  "city": "Berlin",
  "country": "Deutschland"
}

    Second Level Cluster Model ¶

    title
    string (optional) Example: 10115

    type
    string (optional) Example: postcode

    Choices: postcode city country

    count
    number (optional) Example: 4

    The number of locations inside the cluster.

    center_latitude
    number (optional) Example: 52.528809357143

    Latitude of the cluster center.

    center_longitude
    number (optional) Example: 13.379654547619

    Longitude of the cluster center.

    sw_latitude
    number (optional) Example: 52.505681

    South west corner latitude of the cluster bounding boxes.

    sw_longitude
    number (optional) Example: 13.285105

    South west corner longitude of the cluster bounding boxes.

    ne_latitude
    number (optional) Example: 52.576979

    North east corner latitude of the cluster bounding boxes.

    ne_longitude
    number (optional) Example: 13.47168

    North east corner longitude of the cluster bounding boxes.

    city
    string (optional) Example: Berlin

    parent city the cluster belongs to, only shown if the cluster type is postcode

    country
    string (optional) Example: Deutschland

    parent country the cluster belongs to, only shown if the cluster type is postcode or city

    Location Model ¶

    id
    string (optional) Example: e644e4bc-4c5c-11e4-a24a-d43d7eecedd2

    unique identifier of the location used for referencing.

    address_slug
    string (optional) Example: dorfstrasse-11

    latitude
    number (optional) Example: 52.60826

    latitude part of the location geo coordinate

    longitude
    number (optional) Example: 13.19988

    longitude part of the location geo

    street
    string (optional) Example: Dorfstraße

    the street name of the location without number

    street_number
    string (optional) Example: 11

    the street number of the location

    postcode
    string (optional) Example: 16761

    post code of the location

    city
    string (optional) Example: Hennigsdorf

    city of the location

    country
    string (optional) Example: Deutschland

    country of the location in 2 character encoding country of the location in 2

    character encoding

    bookable
    boolean (optional) Example: true

    true if that locations can be booked via the parku API, false if the location

    is purely providing information

    payment
    object 

    available payment methods and types for the current user in this location. The payment methods and types depend on the private key of the logged in user. For locations requests using public keys these arrays will be empty.

    payment.methods
    array Example: [paypal]

    May Contain: paypal credits coupon braintree ideal

    Possible payment methods for this location and user

    payment.types
    array Example: [post]

    May Contain: post immediate

    Possible payment types for this location and user

    availability
    object 

    describes the availability of the location in relation to the request

    availability.current
    number (optional) Example: 0

    the number of parking spaces available in the group for the requested time period defined

    by start and endthe number of parking spaces available in the group for the requested time period defined by start and end

    availability.maximum
    number (optional) Example: 1

    the overall number of parking spaces at this group the overall number of parking spaces at

    this group

    availability.next_start
    string (optional) Example: 2016-...15:00:..

    the start of the next from now slot in which a parking space in this

    group is free and bookable, can be in the past

    availability.next_end
    string (optional) Example: 2016-...15:00:..

    the end of the next slot from now in which a parking space in this group

    is free and bookable, can be in the past

    parking_space_groups
    array 

    different parking space groups for this location. See Parking Space Group Data

    gates
    array 

    the gates connected to the location

    Parking Space Group Model Example

  "id": "1644c5dc-4c5c-11e4-a24a-d43d7eecedd2",
